ShortName: Bagging, random forests & boosting
Topic: statistical-learning
Concepts: bagging (bootstrap aggregation: average B unpruned trees trained on bootstrap samples to reduce variance),
 out-of-bag error (the free test-error estimate from observations left out of each bootstrap sample),
 random forests (decorrelate bagged trees by restricting each split to m random predictors),
 boosting (build small trees sequentially — fitting residuals in regression or pseudo-residuals in classification — with shrinkage for slow accurate learning),
 variable importance (rank predictors by total RSS or Gini improvement across all B trees)
BuildsOn: [decision-trees](decision-trees/lesson.qmd),
 [resampling-bootstrap-and-permutation](resampling-bootstrap-and-permutation/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
